page.title: 15Firsby Nature Reserve
page.content: On May 22nd we went to Firsby Reservoir Nature reserve. We looked at the{ponds}first then we went to the {reservoir.}We walked round the reservoir and looked at the nature. We saw some{mallards}and their families by the side of the water.Walking along we saw an{orange tip butterfly, a red {admiral butterfly, a peacock butterfly and a{Tortoiseshell.}We found a{green {veined white too.}We saw a{buff tip {caterpiller.}We heard a{sedge warbler and saw a{lapwing}and a{swift.}If you looked at the ground you could see little holes where{mining wasps}live. We looked at some flowers and saw {bluebells}everywhere.We also saw some {cowslips,}a big bush of{broom, {stichwort, pink garnet, garlic flower, {yellow archangel}and{dandelions.}There was also{ivy}growing on the walls.
